## Don'ts (apply to both directions)

- Do NOT silently fix a bug without recording the lesson — the next
  agent (or future you) WILL repeat it.
- Do NOT bury the lesson in a code comment alone. Comments are
  invisible to agents working on a different file.
- Do NOT write a vague rule like "be careful with bottom sheets" —
  rules must be actionable and testable.
- Do NOT skip the regression test. A rule without a test is a
  suggestion; a test is enforcement.
- Do NOT mark old rules "deprecated" and leave them in the folder.
  Either delete them or rewrite them in place.
- Do NOT keep two rules that say almost the same thing. Merge them
  and delete the loser.

## Reporting

When you finish a task that triggered either direction, your summary
MUST include a section titled **"What I learned / unlearned"** that:

- Names every file you added, edited, or deleted in `.cursor/rules/`.
- One-line summarises each lesson learned and each belief unlearned.
